---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
---

<PageLayout
	title="About — 332"
	description="[YOUR META DESCRIPTION for the about page]"
>
	<div class="page-root relative min-h-screen px-4 pb-32 pt-32">
		<div class="dot-pattern pointer-events-none absolute inset-0" aria-hidden="true"></div>

		<div class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-0 overflow-hidden" aria-hidden="true">
			<div
				class="absolute -left-[10%] top-[5%] h-[600px] w-[600px] rounded-full"
				style="background: radial-gradient(circle, oklch(0.9 0 0 / 6%), transparent 65%); filter: blur(100px);"
			></div>
			<div
				class="absolute -right-[5%] top-[40%] h-[500px] w-[500px] rounded-full"
				style="background: radial-gradient(circle, oklch(0.8 0 0 / 5%), transparent 65%); filter: blur(80px);"
			></div>
		</div>

		<div class="relative z-10 mx-auto max-w-4xl">

			<!-- Page header -->
			<div class="mb-16 text-center animate-[fade-in-up_0.7s_ease-out_both]">
				<p class="section-label">Who We Are</p>
				<h1 class="mb-4 text-4xl tracking-wider text-foreground sm:text-5xl">
					About 332<span class="blink-cursor">_</span>
				</h1>
				<p class="mx-auto max-w-xl text-base leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
					[A one-liner about 332 — the short version of what you tell people when they ask what this place is.]
				</p>
			</div>

			<!-- Origin story -->
			<section class="mb-12">
				<div class="glass-card rounded-2xl p-8 sm:p-12">
					<p class="section-label">Background</p>
					<h2 class="mb-6 text-2xl tracking-wider text-foreground">
						Where we came from<span class="blink-cursor">_</span>
					</h2>
					<div class="space-y-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground sm:text-base">
						<p>
							[The origin story of 332 — formerly Order 332. How it started, what the name means or where it came from, who was there at the beginning. Be honest and direct.]
						</p>
						<p>
							[The evolution — how the community has changed, grown, shifted focus. What's stayed the same.]
						</p>
						<p>
							[What 332 is today — the current state, what keeps people around, what the community is known for among members.]
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<!-- Values grid -->
			<section class="mb-12">
				<p class="section-label mb-6">What We Stand For</p>
				<div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">

					<div class="glass-card rounded-2xl p-6">
						<div class="mb-4 flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-xl glass-button text-muted-foreground">
							<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M21 15a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H7l-4 4V5a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h14a2 2 0 0 1 2 2z"/></svg>
						</div>
						<h3 class="mb-2 text-base tracking-wider text-foreground">Free Speech</h3>
						<p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
							[Your stance on free speech. What it means practically — not just a slogan. What you will and won't tolerate and why.]
						</p>
					</div>

					<div class="glass-card rounded-2xl p-6">
						<div class="mb-4 flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-xl glass-button text-muted-foreground">
							<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="4 17 10 11 4 5"/><line x1="12" x2="20" y1="19" y2="19"/></svg>
						</div>
						<h3 class="mb-2 text-base tracking-wider text-foreground">Cyber First</h3>
						<p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
							[Your relationship with cybersecurity — is it a profession, a hobby, a mindset? What kind of cyber topics does the community focus on? CTF, red team, research, OSINT, etc.]
						</p>
					</div>

					<div class="glass-card rounded-2xl p-6">
						<div class="mb-4 flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-xl glass-button text-muted-foreground">
							<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M12 2a15.3 15.3 0 0 1 4 10 15.3 15.3 0 0 1-4 10 15.3 15.3 0 0 1-4-10 15.3 15.3 0 0 1 4-10z"/><path d="M2 12h20"/></svg>
						</div>
						<h3 class="mb-2 text-base tracking-wider text-foreground">Global Reach</h3>
						<p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
							[How the global nature of 332 shapes it — different timezones, backgrounds, expertise. How many members or countries if you want to share.]
						</p>
					</div>

					<div class="glass-card rounded-2xl p-6">
						<div class="mb-4 flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-xl glass-button text-muted-foreground">
							<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect width="18" height="11" x="3" y="11" rx="2" ry="2"/><path d="M7 11V7a5 5 0 0 1 10 0v4"/></svg>
						</div>
						<h3 class="mb-2 text-base tracking-wider text-foreground">Invite Only</h3>
						<p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
							[Why 332 is private and invite-only. What that filter is meant to preserve — quality, trust, signal-to-noise, culture. How the invite process works if you want to explain it.]
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<!-- Members section -->
			<section class="mb-12">
				<div class="glass-card rounded-2xl p-8 sm:p-12">
					<p class="section-label">The Community</p>
					<h2 class="mb-6 text-2xl tracking-wider text-foreground">
						Who's here<span class="blink-cursor">_</span>
					</h2>

					<div class="mb-8 grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-3">
						<div class="text-center">
							<div class="mb-1 text-3xl tracking-wider text-foreground">[COUNT]<span class="text-muted-foreground">+</span></div>
							<div class="text-xs tracking-widest text-muted-foreground uppercase">Members</div>
						</div>
						<div class="text-center">
							<div class="mb-1 text-3xl tracking-wider text-foreground">[COUNT]</div>
							<div class="text-xs tracking-widest text-muted-foreground uppercase">Countries</div>
						</div>
						<div class="text-center">
							<div class="mb-1 text-3xl tracking-wider text-foreground">[YEAR]</div>
							<div class="text-xs tracking-widest text-muted-foreground uppercase">Founded</div>
						</div>
					</div>

					<p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground sm:text-base">
						[A description of who actually makes up 332 — backgrounds, skills, what they're into. Security researchers, developers, students, professionals? What's the vibe?]
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>

			<!-- What happens here section -->
			<section class="mb-12">
				<p class="section-label mb-6">Inside 332</p>
				<div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">

					<div class="glass-card rounded-2xl p-5">
						<h3 class="mb-2 text-sm tracking-wider text-foreground">Channels & Discussion</h3>
						<p class="text-xs leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
							[What kinds of conversations happen in 332 — technical, casual, news, projects? What are the main areas of discussion?]
						</p>
					</div>

					<div class="glass-card rounded-2xl p-5">
						<h3 class="mb-2 text-sm tracking-wider text-foreground">CTF & Competitions</h3>
						<p class="text-xs leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
							[How the community participates in CTFs — team play, the 332 CTF platform, challenges, writeups, etc.]
						</p>
					</div>

					<div class="glass-card rounded-2xl p-5">
						<h3 class="mb-2 text-sm tracking-wider text-foreground">Projects & Building</h3>
						<p class="text-xs leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
							[How members build things together — open projects, collaboration, the tools and platforms members have created.]
						</p>
					</div>

					<div class="glass-card rounded-2xl p-5">
						<h3 class="mb-2 text-sm tracking-wider text-foreground">Voice & Events</h3>
						<p class="text-xs leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
							[Regular voice sessions, presentations, watch parties, gaming sessions — whatever happens in VC/events.]
						</p>
					</div>

					<div class="glass-card rounded-2xl p-5">
						<h3 class="mb-2 text-sm tracking-wider text-foreground">Knowledge Sharing</h3>
						<p class="text-xs leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
							[How knowledge moves through 332 — writeups, resources, tutorials, help channels, mentorship, etc.]
						</p>
					</div>

					<div class="glass-card rounded-2xl p-5">
						<h3 class="mb-2 text-sm tracking-wider text-foreground">Tools & Bots</h3>
						<p class="text-xs leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
							[Telos and any other tooling that makes the server tick — commands, integrations, automations, the AI assistant.]
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<!-- Rules / expectations -->
			<section class="mb-12">
				<div class="glass-card rounded-2xl p-8 sm:p-12">
					<p class="section-label">Standards</p>
					<h2 class="mb-6 text-2xl tracking-wider text-foreground">
						How we operate<span class="blink-cursor">_</span>
					</h2>
					<div class="space-y-3">
						{[
							['[Rule 1]', '[Explanation of rule 1 — be specific, not generic]'],
							['[Rule 2]', '[Explanation of rule 2]'],
							['[Rule 3]', '[Explanation of rule 3]'],
							['[Rule 4]', '[Explanation of rule 4]'],
							['[Rule 5]', '[Explanation of rule 5]'],
						].map(([title, desc]) => (
							<div class="flex gap-4 border-b border-white/5 pb-3 last:border-0 last:pb-0">
								<span class="mt-0.5 shrink-0 text-xs tracking-widest text-muted-foreground uppercase">{title}</span>
								<p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">{desc}</p>
							</div>
						))}
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<!-- CTA -->
			<section class="text-center">
				<div class="glass-card rounded-2xl px-8 py-12 sm:px-16">
					<h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl tracking-wider text-foreground">
						Want in<span class="blink-cursor">_</span>
					</h2>
					<p class="mb-8 text-sm leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground sm:text-base">
						[How do people get invited? What should they know before applying or reaching out? Is there a waitlist, a process, a specific way to get a voucher?]
					</p>
					<a
						href="[DISCORD_INVITE_URL]"
						class="glass-button glass-button-glass inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-xl px-6 py-3 text-sm tracking-wider text-foreground no-underline transition-all"
						target="_blank"
						rel="noopener noreferrer"
					>
						Join on Discord
						<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-4 w-4" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
							<path d="M18 13v6a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V8a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h6"/>
							<polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"/>
							<line x1="10" y1="14" x2="21" y2="3"/>
						</svg>
					</a>
				</div>
			</section>

		</div>
	</div>

	<!-- Footer -->
	<footer class="border-t border-white/5 px-4 py-8">
		<div class="mx-auto flex max-w-4xl flex-col items-center justify-between gap-4 sm:flex-row">
			<div class="flex items-center gap-2.5">
				<img src="/polygon.svg" alt="332" class="h-5 w-5 opacity-60" width="20" height="20" />
				<span class="text-sm tracking-widest text-muted-foreground">332</span>
			</div>
			<div class="flex items-center gap-6 text-xs tracking-wider text-muted-foreground">
				<a href="/" class="hover:text-foreground transition-colors no-underline">Home</a>
				<a href="/projects" class="hover:text-foreground transition-colors no-underline">Projects</a>
				<a href="/blog" class="hover:text-foreground transition-colors no-underline">Blog</a>
				<a href="[DISCORD_INVITE_URL]" class="hover:text-foreground transition-colors no-underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Discord</a>
			</div>
			<p class="text-xs tracking-wider text-muted-foreground opacity-40">
				© {new Date().getFullYear()} 332
			</p>
		</div>
	</footer>
</PageLayout>
